article.headline: Texas-Pan American 74, Texas-San Antonio 72
article.story: EDINBURG, Texas -- Emmanuel Jones scored 24 points in Texas-Pan American's 74-72 win over Texas-San Antonio on Thursday night. Texas-Pan American (4-7) led by as much as 11 in the second half before Texas-San Antonio closed the gap. After Devin Gibson hit a 3-pointer to make it 68-67 with 4:47 left, Jones scored six points. Gibson answered with five points on two jumpers and a free throw. Nathan Hawkins added 15 points for Texas-Pan American. Jared Maree scored 12 and Nick Weiermiller had 11. Gibson led Texas-San Antonio (3-4) with 16 points. Travis Gabbidon added 11. Texas-Pan American led 39-32 at the half.
